After six months of re-dedicating my available time to artwork I’m finally at a place where I feel confident enough to begin the commissions for clients whom have been waiting patiently on the side lines for me to get to this mental space. I’m so excited and grateful. Now, I can’t wait for life to slow down in order to find the time to dedicate to create them. I’ll be working on a very special mandala tattoo, and another special watercolour of a home. It’s always so rewarding to be trusted with artwork that is very special to the client, and I’m grateful to be able to experience that again. These are things that remind me why I’m doing this and it’s my cue to remind all of you to truly listen to your heart follow the thing that is calling for you. Xo
